92085,0.071365,0.10203,0.10632,0.10204,0.096752,0.095682,0.088493,0.079014,0.064476,0.044707]},{"section":5,"text":"The fact that she's passing some fluid and tissue makes me think about miscarriage or perhaps a partial expulsion.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.067917,0.093718,0.098207,0.10204,0.094055,0.090825,0.090697,0.084151,0.078667,0.076846,0.066326,0.05655],"unified_progress":[0.060924,0.083102,0.088322,0.093126,0.0938,0.093827,0.092624,0.093496,0.087618,0.083244,0.071984,0.057934]},{"section":6,"text":"The uterus being larger than expected could indicate something like a gestational age discrepancy, maybe a multiple pregnancy or something else affecting the size.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.049551,0.067701,0.085734,0.097033,0.097755,0.098064,0.099138,0.094772,0.089379,0.087509,0.072773,0.060591],"unified_progress":[0.047811,0.071296,0.086462,0.09526,0.097124,0.097574,0.097971,0.096245,0.092051,0.086788,0.073981,0.057438]},{"section":7,"text":"Now, the key part is the description of the uterus filled with cystic, avascular, grapelike structures.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046213,0.076745,0.084053,0.094077,0.094962,0.096018,0.097175,0.09205,0.085721,0.082167,0.078097,0.072723],"unified_progress":[0.041176,0.071077,0.083849,0.095172,0.097568,0.096647,0.095985,0.092814,0.092088,0.085668,0.077492,0.070464]},{"section":8,"text":"Those terms make me think of something called gestational trophoblastic disease.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040944,0.06436,0.078751,0.091177,0.094795,0.097424,0.10118,0.098041,0.093993,0.091558,0.078845,0.068934],"unified_progress":[0.036481,0.063965,0.081887,0.094176,0.097464,0.10235,0.10108,0.097576,0.0942,0.09,0.076951,0.063866]},{"section":9,"text":"I remember that in GTD, the placenta can become abnormal, and there are different types like complete and incomplete hydatidiform mole.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.022901,0.045558,0.065431,0.079605,0.098064,0.10797,0.11265,0.11677,0.11296,0.096767,0.076673,0.064658],"unified_progress":[0.026804,0.055744,0.079742,0.093983,0.10133,0.11553,0.10998,0.10545,0.098502,0.0906,0.07027,0.052062]},{"section":10,"text":"The cystic structures without penetration into the uterine wall are characteristic of a hydatidiform mole, specifically the complete type.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028677,0.044655,0.063185,0.078517,0.094682,0.10453,0.11012,0.11381,0.10921,0.095781,0.082353,0.07448],"unified_progress":[0.030801,0.055718,0.07637,0.092152,0.098965,0.10709,0.10562,0.1032,0.099544,0.090878,0.076,0.063666]},{"section":11,"text":"Wait, but she's 15 weeks along, which is a bit later than the usual presentation for molar pregnancy, which is often earlier in the first trimester.","dimension":0,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.04141,0.064734,0.074465,0.080396,0.086706,0.092071,0.096953,0.099661,0.10067,0.099215,0.089,0.074722],"unified_progress":[0.046637,0.070314,0.079322,0.086972,0.092182,0.096708,0.096509,0.098409,0.094479,0.093515,0.07998,0.064972]},{"section":12,"text":"However, I've heard that some cases can present later.","dimension":8,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042784,0.067036,0.076162,0.080904,0.08679,0.091535,0.096475,0.099354,0.10121,0.10021,0.088702,0.068833],"unified_progress":[0.047308,0.073217,0.083529,0.091146,0.093995,0.096677,0.097367,0.097388,0.09265,0.091294,0.076608,0.058821]},{"section":13,"text":"Also, the presence of bleeding and expulsion of tissue aligns with a molar pregnancy, as the placenta can start to separate and cause these symptoms.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.049268,0.058121,0.068973,0.076612,0.083978,0.090224,0.094654,0.098765,0.099847,0.096417,0.091939,0.091202],"unified_progress":[0.04878,0.062992,0.07623,0.083595,0.088906,0.09603,0.094868,0.096428,0.094056,0.090958,0.086028,0.081129]},{"section":14,"text":"Another thought: could it be something else, like an ectopic pregnancy?","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.022958,0.050867,0.069506,0.081374,0.088603,0.095471,0.10218,0.10779,0.11048,0.11259,0.093749,0.064436],"unified_progress":[0.031318,0.065931,0.084282,0.096643,0.098612,0.097968,0.10217,0.10107,0.097613,0.09367,0.077024,0.053701]},{"section":15,"text":"But ectopic pregnancies can cause more severe symptoms like severe pain and signs of shock, which she doesn't mention here.","dimension":5,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02417,0.049671,0.067412,0.076816,0.084779,0.093034,0.10053,0.10939,0.11302,0.11144,0.1038,0.065944],"unified_progress":[0.029474,0.056909,0.072379,0.080359,0.093356,0.096167,0.10099,0.10903,0.10684,0.11022,0.089518,0.054762]},{"section":16,"text":"Plus, the description of the uterine structures seems more consistent with molar changes.","dimension":5,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042228,0.049355,0.060968,0.070063,0.076709,0.084365,0.091347,0.098131,0.10328,0.10592,0.11009,0.10754],"unified_progress":[0.039071,0.054502,0.066007,0.075404,0.082862,0.088304,0.092818,0.097926,0.10012,0.10257,0.10138,0.099028]},{"section":17,"text":"So putting it all together, the combination of uterine size, cystic structures, avascular, and the clinical presentation points towards a gestational trophoblastic disease, specifically a complete hydatidiform mole.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.016216,0.026498,0.035176,0.041657,0.047052,0.054275,0.062258,0.076531,0.09319,0.11812,0.16615,0.26288],"unified_progress":[0.015353,0.02637,0.034805,0.044369,0.049674,0.062973,0.068384,0.082801,0.097938,0.11087,0.16368,0.24279]},{"section":18,"text":"I think that's the most likely diagnosis here.","dimension":11,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026231,0.047428,0.04851,0.