 could be due to polyhydramnios, but that's usually associated with excess amniotic fluid, not necessarily with tissue passing.","dimension":3,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027765,0.05706,0.075623,0.087275,0.096071,0.1011,0.10599,0.10676,0.10412,0.09517,0.080761,0.062305],"unified_progress":[0.030276,0.060858,0.083048,0.094829,0.10171,0.10952,0.10707,0.10407,0.09827,0.09016,0.071151,0.049039]},{"section":9,"text":"Or maybe it's a molar pregnancy.","dimension":5,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.024023,0.046621,0.063734,0.078852,0.09151,0.10287,0.11209,0.1153,0.11545,0.10294,0.086154,0.060451],"unified_progress":[0.030687,0.067948,0.087863,0.10002,0.10381,0.10256,0.10523,0.10233,0.096648,0.088934,0.069163,0.044806]},{"section":10,"text":"Molar pregnancies are a type of gestational trophoblastic disease where the conceptus develops into a mass of cysts instead of a normal embryo.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034,0.055956,0.071514,0.08377,0.094798,0.10059,0.1086,0.10823,0.10363,0.093124,0.080118,0.065666],"unified_progress":[0.037851,0.06716,0.086504,0.09772,0.10503,0.10784,0.10424,0.099621,0.094903,0.081637,0.066635,0.050862]},{"section":11,"text":"In a molar pregnancy, the uterus is often larger than expected for the gestational age because the trophoblast cells grow rapidly.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031872,0.056769,0.075031,0.087594,0.09805,0.10264,0.10721,0.10518,0.10128,0.090535,0.078697,0.065134],"unified_progress":[0.035332,0.06688,0.087499,0.099631,0.10574,0.11062,0.10446,0.0981,0.094797,0.081046,0.065106,0.050781]},{"section":12,"text":"The structures inside are cystic and grapelike, which aligns with the description.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035533,0.062993,0.080547,0.093388,0.099854,0.10154,0.10445,0.099642,0.094757,0.084665,0.076005,0.066623],"unified_progress":[0.03446,0.068186,0.087843,0.10029,0.